Results
Overall, 142 research articles were identified. Of this, three cross-sectional studies involving 702 children with SCD from Uganda (n = 1) and Nigeria (n = 2) met the eligibility criteria and were included. Four hundred thirty-four individuals from the included studies used herbal medicines for the management of SCD. The prevalence of current herbal medicine use in individual studies ranged from 36.4% to 78.0%, with a pooled prevalence of 59% (95% confidence interval: 35.0–82.0, I2 = 97.68%, P < 0.001).
